Cause: Related to wages, Related to demand to be sent home, Related to Food
Brief_details: Many workers from Purulia district came to work in brickyards of Paschim Barddhaman district was stuck in their workplaces for months due to lockdown. They did not get proper food, were denied  any transport to go home by local administration and were not even paid their wage from the owner of brickyard.   In this circumstances more than 500 workers started their journey to go home by walking. But at Mejiya bridge of Raniganj they were stopped by police on 7th May. They were not given any food. Next day the workers launched a protest and blocked NH 60,located in that region. They demanded arrangement for going home and food.

Brief_details: Large gathering demanding to be sent home, stone pelting and mediation for talks with the management done by the police.

Cause: Related to demand to be sent home, Related to Food, Related to facilities at relief/quarantine shelters, Dispute regarding ration mal-distribution
Brief_details: Large gathering, demands raised, stone pelting. Police mediated between the workers and management for talks.

Cause: Related to demand to be sent home
Brief_details: Migrants from Jammu and Kashmir protested against the Jammu and Kashmir governments demanding that they make arrangements for their journey home. Local SDM assured that arrangements will be made once Jammu and Kashmir govts give permission for the same.

Cause: Related to wages, Related to Food, Dispute regarding ration mal-distribution
Brief_details: Around 400 contract workers of Globus Spirits Ltd. staged demonstration in front of the plant demanding 2 months of due wages.

Cause: Related to Food, Against govt policies
Brief_details: Dharna protest, sit in encircling the local Kathunipal police station and tomb. Hundreds of residents of Parkote, Kota gathered in the area against the "Mahacurfew" imposed in the area for the past one month. Removed police barricades and demanded end to blanket curfew even in areas with no patients as they are running out of money due to no work.

Cause: Related to demand to be sent home
Brief_details: Migrant youth from UP and Bihar protested, demanding that they be given permission to go back home. They had registered and were willing to make paid, private arrangements for the same, but had not been given permission which led to the protest. Authorities assured them that their demands will be met.

Cause: Against govt policies, Against Krishak Kalyan Fee (Farmer Relief Cess)
Brief_details: Agricultural Products traders on strike since 6th May to oppose Rajasthan govt's imposition of Krishak Kalyan Fee of 2%, across 247 mandis in Rajasthan. No buying of farmers produce happening currently in these mandis. Extended the strike from 10th May to 15th May as govt didn't remove the fee.

Cause: Related to demand to be sent home, Related to Food, Against govt policies
Brief_details: Protest demonstration by migrant residents of the area (mostly from UP, Bihar, Bengal). Police and authorities are present at the spot and process of dialogue is beginning. Protesting workers are demanding that they be allowed to go back home as due to no work (owing 50 days of lockdown in the area) they are finding it difficult to get adequate ration and are running out of money.  आज जयपुर के नाहरी का नाका इलाके में रहने वाले हजारों  प्रवासी मजदूरों द्वारा अपने घर जाने की मांग को लेकर,, विरोध प्रदर्शन किया जा रहा है ,,पुलिस और प्रशासन के लोग मौके पर मौजूद है । पिछले  50 दिन से लॉक डाउन में फंसे होने के कारणना तो इनको काम मिल रहा है,, और नाही  खाने पीने को मिल रहा है। इस कारण परेशान मजदूरों ने आज बाहर आकर सड़क पर विरोध प्रदर्शन कर रहे है और सरकार से मांग कर रहे है कि उन्हें उनके घर यूपी बिहार बंगाल जहां के रहने वाले हैं वहां पर उन्हें जाने दिया जाए।प्रशासन से वार्ता चल रही है ।
